Petroleo Brasileiro SA,  Brazil â€™s
state-controlled oil producer, plans to sell $7 billion in bonds
in overseas markets as soon as today, according to a person
familiar with the transaction.  Petrobras plans to sell $1.25 billion of new three-year
bonds to yield 275 basis points, or 2.75 percentage points,
above U.S. Treasuries, and $1.75 billion of five-year debt at a
spread of 290 basis points. The company also plans to sell $2.75
billion more of its bonds maturing in 2021 to yield 295 basis
points above Treasuries, and $1.25 billion more of the 2041
securities at a spread of 295 basis points, the person said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
